Package ru.viise.papka.entity

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Folder<T>
    Folder contains files and children.
    FoldersFile<T,V>
    FoldersFile is necessary from generating tree folder.
    Name
    Name exists, because all operations about files and folders do not occur without the participation of their name.
    Node<T>
    Each tree folder filesystem has a node.
    PreparedFolders<T>
    PreparedFolders prepares raw files for the subsequent tree folder building.
    TreeFolder<T>
    TreeFolder builds a folder tree.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    FolderFile
    Folder with File files from raw files.
    FolderFileWin
    Folder with File files from raw files for Windows.
    FolderPure<T>
    Pure implementation of Folder interface.
    FoldersFileName
    Folders like names from full filename.
    FoldersFileNameWin
    Folders like names from full filename for Windows.
    FolderText
    Folder with String files from raw files.
    NameFolderRoot
    Name of root folder.
    NameFoldersPath
    Full folder path from folder names.
    NamePure
    Pure implementation of Name interface.
    NameSystemDriveWin
    Name of Windows system drive.
    PreparedFoldersMapFile
    Prepares folders as Map<String, Folder<File>>, where key is full folder name, and value is the folder with files.
    PreparedFoldersMapFilesRaw
    Prepares folders as Map<String, List<File>>, where key is full folder name, and value is the list of folder files.
    PreparedFoldersMapFileSystem
    Prepares folders as Map<String, Folder<File>>, where key is full folder name, and value is the folder with files.
    PreparedFoldersMapFileWin
    Prepares folders as Map<String, Folder<File>>, where key is full folder name, and value is the folder with files of Windows.
    PreparedFoldersMapRaw
    Prepares folders as Map<String, List<String>>, where key is full folder name, and value is the list of short folder filenames.
    PreparedFoldersMapText
    Prepares folders as Map<String, Folder<String>>, where key is full folder name, and value is the folder with files like short filenames.
    TreeFolderPure<T>
    Pure implementation of TreeFolder interface.
